data.text:
(Biography)

A Canadian singer-song writer, Avril Lavigne is given by birth name as “Avril Ramona Lavigne”. She used to be called before as “Abbey Dawn” when she’s not that famous before. She was born on September 27, 1984 in Belleville, Ontario, Canada and spent most of her childhood in Napanee, Ontario.

Avril, began singing in church at a young age. She learned to play the guitar and began composing her own music as a teenager. At first, she was been focused on country music but then it was eventually changing her tune. She left her highschool and went to New York City and then to Los Angeles to start working with Artista Records.

Two years later, she released her debut album “Let Go”. Two of the songs from that album entitled, “Complicated” and “Sk8er Boi” became a hit and sold more than 15million copies worldwide. Her album lately follwed up with the albums “Under My Skin” in 2004, “The Best Damn Thing” in 2007 and “Goodbye Lullaby” in 2011.
